`T getById(ID id)` has been deprecated since 2.7. [Please use `T getReferenceById(ID id)` instead.][3] The idea is the same, it returns a reference only. But it is more self-explained, as &quot;getById&quot; maybe unclear and &quot;getReferenceById&quot; would be less ambiguous.

    Customer customerToUpdate = customerRepository.getReferenceById(id);
    customerToUpdate.setName(customerDto.getName);
