----------


jni::sys was written for internal use, do not use it.

jni is an interface for using native binaries in java.

In java, you can use
```java
static {
  System.load(&quot;/Path/to/so/or/dll.dll&quot;);
  System.loadLibrary(&quot;nameOfLibraryWithoutExtension&quot;);
}
```
to load it.

If you want to use native function in java, you can use
```java
  private(or public) native (returnType) (functionName)(args);
  private native void myFunc2();
  ...
  void foo() {
    var ret = (name)(1,2,3);
    myFunc2();
  }
```


----------
In this case, you can use `javap -s compiled.class.path` to descripter,

after than, write this code,
```rust
